column4: i don't understand.. when I run "sudo apt-get update" I get a message at the end telling me I need to run apt-get update to correct some problem??? but that is what I have just done to get the message. what's up with that?

it tells me "W: Duplicate sources.list entry http://security.ubuntu.com edgy-security/main Packages (/var/lib/apt/lists/security.ubuntu.com_ubuntu_dists_edgy-security_main_binary-i386_Packages) W: You may want to run apt-get update to correct these problems"
